examples.en: The children darted into the room.
The frog darted its tongue at a fly.
The rabbit darted into the chaparral.
His forefinger darted in all directions as he spoke.
Ellie darted back to her room and shut herself in.
With surprising agility, Karl darted across the road.
Coloured fish darted hither and thither (=backwards and forwards).
He was a flamboyant, excited person whose eyes darted here and there, like a child's, afraid of what they might miss.
